04:27.080 --> 04:28.646
once again
you have proven to be
my best customer.

04:30.077 --> 04:32.821
this is a birthday gift
that ned will never expect.

04:32.822 --> 04:34.588
you know, do you think
he's going to get it?

04:34.655 --> 04:36.022
i mean,
will he know what it is?

04:36.089 --> 04:38.489
oh, yeah, this is
all making a comeback.

04:38.556 --> 04:39.688
because they discovered

04:39.755 --> 04:41.855
vinyl produces
a better sound than digital.

04:41.922 --> 04:44.355
can you believe that?
do they still make vinyl?

04:44.717 --> 04:47.851
well, you know,
it's hard to find,
but it's out there.

04:47.916 --> 04:49.970
besides, i still have
my whole collection
in a box somewhere.

04:49.971 --> 04:53.103
right, i bet ned
can't wait to listen
to tom jones and neil young.

04:54.196 --> 04:56.179
ok, so, we'll skip
my collection,

04:56.180 --> 04:58.746
but a lot of bands
are releasing on vinyl
these days.

04:58.853 --> 05:01.621
you know what?
i think it's great,
totally original.

05:01.686 --> 05:03.454
hey....

05:03.521 --> 05:05.254
did i dream
that phone call last night?

05:06.852 --> 05:08.200
yes, you did.

05:08.201 --> 05:10.032
oh, you are such a liar.

05:10.033 --> 05:11.867
what was that?
were you sleep-dialing?

05:11.933 --> 05:13.767
nothing, i just--

05:13.834 --> 05:14.940
i just had
a weird dream.

05:15.770 --> 05:18.004
about me?

05:18.071 --> 05:18.843
i don't remember

05:18.844 --> 05:19.978
what it was about.

05:20.044 --> 05:21.678
but don't worry, ok?

05:21.744 --> 05:23.178
now, when are you going
to give this to ned?

05:23.245 --> 05:26.011
oh, well, tim is
trying to find
some really cool records.

05:26.078 --> 05:27.511
before his birthday,
i hope.

05:27.578 --> 05:29.744
so, that's going well?

05:31.480 --> 05:34.176
yeah, i mean,
i don't know,

05:34.177 --> 05:36.166
it just kinda
feels comfortable.

05:36.167 --> 05:37.267
you know?

05:37.333 --> 05:38.434
even if we're
just sitting there,

05:38.500 --> 05:42.033
not even talking,
it just feels right.

05:42.632 --> 05:43.830
that's great.

05:43.831 --> 05:46.565
yeah, well, baby steps.

05:46.632 --> 05:48.565
hey, do you mind
if i hide this in the back?

05:48.632 --> 05:49.964
uh, if you can find
a place for it

05:50.031 --> 05:50.964
in the black hole
back there,

05:51.031 --> 05:51.964
be my guest.

05:52.190 --> 05:52.886
hey! you know what?

05:52.887 --> 05:54.187
i'm going to go
get some coffee,
do you want something?

05:54.253 --> 05:56.299
yeah, that'd be great.
surprise me.

05:56.300 --> 05:57.934
ok.

08:28.537 --> 08:31.157
who are you?

08:31.158 --> 08:33.126
they told me
you would know.

08:33.345 --> 08:34.779
who told you?

08:34.846 --> 08:36.813
they said you would help.

08:36.943 --> 08:39.543
i don't understand.

08:41.423 --> 08:42.822
mary o'connell.

08:43.792 --> 08:45.192
mary o'connell?

08:45.193 --> 08:45.929
that was the beginning.

08:45.930 --> 08:46.947
the beginning of what?

08:58.711 --> 09:01.245
you remember what happened,
don't you, lynn?

09:01.312 --> 09:03.078
don't you remember?

09:03.145 --> 09:05.511
that day, the accident?

09:18.845 --> 09:20.245
your dad
tells me you've been

09:20.944 --> 09:22.810
making these drawings
ever since.

09:24.377 --> 09:28.143
well, tell me, please,
why have you been
making these drawings?

09:28.210 --> 09:29.744
'cause i have to.

09:29.810 --> 09:33.011
but why do you have to?

09:33.076 --> 09:35.577
it's in my head,
isn't it?

09:35.644 --> 09:38.243
every day, i have to.

10:15.610 --> 10:16.810
same as it never was.

10:16.877 --> 10:18.176
hey, it's me,
i'm looking right at you.

10:18.243 --> 10:20.922
i forgot to ask
if you wanted anything
from java?

10:20.923 --> 10:22.740
uh, no, i'm good.
you go ahead.

10:23.487 --> 10:25.959
you know,
i think i'll wait.

10:25.960 --> 10:28.227
i want to try
and get a head start--

10:28.294 --> 10:30.094
whoa!

10:32.480 --> 10:33.713
i am so sorry.

10:33.780 --> 10:35.079
are you ok?

10:35.146 --> 10:36.761
i didn't even see you.

10:36.762 --> 10:37.995
no, it really was my fault,

10:38.062 --> 10:39.595
i wasn't even
paying attention.

10:39.662 --> 10:41.129
stay off cell phones.

10:41.196 --> 10:42.296
delia, are you all right?

10:42.362 --> 10:43.929
do you want to just
go sit for a minute?

10:43.995 --> 10:45.929
no, i'm ok, really,
please, i'm fine.

10:45.995 --> 10:50.296
it was a close call,
but that's it.

10:50.362 --> 10:52.296
hey, everything's fine.

10:52.362 --> 10:53.463
next show is 2 p.m.

10:53.529 --> 10:54.862
i'm going
to be here all week.

10:54.929 --> 10:58.129
it's fine, please,
i'm gonna just, um...

10:58.196 --> 10:59.529
i'm going to go
sit down in the shop.

11:21.191 --> 11:24.625
ok, i get it.
it's about water.

12:57.528 --> 12:59.960
all right, so this woman
died on a ferry 2 years ago,

13:00.027 --> 13:02.060
or maybe she didn't,
maybe she doesn't
know how she died,

13:02.127 --> 13:03.427
and you have to tell her,
i don't know.

13:03.494 --> 13:05.027
it sounds
simple to me, whatever.

13:05.094 --> 13:07.268
yeah, but what about
the visions
of impending death?

13:07.319 --> 13:08.919
you think they all
refer to delia?

13:09.109 --> 13:11.097
look, there were
5 signs this past year.

13:11.098 --> 13:12.898
the dead dove, the bee,
the dead will walk,

13:12.964 --> 13:14.432
 the return
 of the forgotten.

13:14.498 --> 13:16.532
the only thing
that hasn't happened
is death of a loved one.

13:16.597 --> 13:18.265
don't you think that
it--it could be related?

13:18.331 --> 13:20.465
how do i know? you're
the one that gets
all the neat visions.

13:20.532 --> 13:22.498
you drink the champagne,
i only get the hangover.

13:22.869 --> 13:25.098
sorry,
guess i caught you
at a bad time.

13:25.099 --> 13:26.666
oh, no, no, you caught me
at a great time.

13:27.889 --> 13:29.132
you seem to be packing.

13:29.133 --> 13:30.200
yes, i'm packing.

13:30.266 --> 13:32.233
i am going
on a sabbatical.

13:32.300 --> 13:33.834
i have
a fantastic opportunity

13:33.835 --> 13:35.801
to do research
in a peruvian jungle.

13:36.015 --> 13:37.582
just like that,
up and gone?

13:37.649 --> 13:38.683
just like that.

13:38.749 --> 13:39.576
nothing supernatural,
either.

13:39.577 --> 13:41.443
although, i should check
and see if jungle insects
have souls,

13:41.510 --> 13:43.710
i'd hate to be haunted
by an earth-bound cicada.

13:45.310 --> 13:48.977
you know we never really...

13:49.043 --> 13:52.911
we never got to talk about
everything that happened.

13:52.977 --> 13:57.043
talking's not always
the best thing.

13:57.110 --> 13:59.710
i'm in that odd place
where i may speak

13:59.777 --> 14:02.877
the unadulterated truth
about everything
i think and feel.

14:04.063 --> 14:04.818
can't have that.

14:04.819 --> 14:06.852
no, we can't have that.

14:08.086 --> 14:10.427
anyway, nope,
this is going to be great.

14:10.428 --> 14:13.527
really a--just a great time
for me to take a break.

14:13.594 --> 14:15.441
i mean you do this
10 times a week.

14:15.442 --> 14:17.426
you know,
you talk to ghosts,
argue with ghosts,

14:17.427 --> 14:18.908
 you get your heart
 broken by a ghost,

14:18.909 --> 14:21.176
but for us mere mortals,
come on.

14:21.646 --> 14:24.646
hey, hey, hey, come on.

14:24.713 --> 14:26.646
this is a good thing,
be happy for me.

14:26.713 --> 14:28.212
i'm going to be doing
what i do and loving it.

14:28.719 --> 14:30.176
i hope you'll
keep in touch.

14:30.177 --> 14:31.097
maybe, maybe not.

14:31.098 --> 14:34.202
maybe we'll just
be 2 ships passing
in the night.

14:34.203 --> 14:36.570
don't say ships.

14:42.068 --> 14:43.135
hey, good morning.

14:43.136 --> 14:44.136
oh, thank you!

14:45.469 --> 14:47.436
boy, do i need this.

14:47.437 --> 14:49.638
yeah, you don't look like
you got enough sleep.

14:49.704 --> 14:50.604
you look great, too.

14:51.384 --> 14:54.150
as do you, tired or not.

14:54.217 --> 14:55.678
nice backpedal.

14:55.679 --> 14:57.579
listen, i really have
to talk to you.

14:58.091 --> 14:59.224
ok.

14:59.297 --> 15:01.586
hey,
look what i found.

15:01.587 --> 15:03.054
 pink floyd
 <i>wish you were here,</i>

15:03.393 --> 15:04.460
 <i>led zep 4.</i>

15:04.527 --> 15:06.427
mint condition,
still shrink-wrapped.

15:06.493 --> 15:08.193
those are great.

15:08.744 --> 15:09.944
where did you find these?

15:10.011 --> 15:11.844
i'd rather not say.

15:13.178 --> 15:15.677
in case i outlive
my usefulness, someday.

15:15.744 --> 15:16.811
that way you'll
always come back to me

15:16.877 --> 15:18.378
for the vinyl.

15:18.445 --> 15:19.677
this is fantastic.

15:19.744 --> 15:22.111
now all we need
is some today vinyl.

15:22.178 --> 15:23.710
you know, bands ned
has actually heard of.

15:23.777 --> 15:25.311
i'm all over it.

15:25.509 --> 15:28.246
hey, you said
you needed to talk
to me about something?

15:28.247 --> 15:29.880
oh, no, no,
never mind.

15:30.140 --> 15:31.474
come for lunch?

15:31.539 --> 15:33.173
i've got invoices
to do, but hey,

15:33.240 --> 15:34.474
bring me back
something gooey.

15:34.539 --> 15:36.340
all right.

15:38.173 --> 15:39.940
bye.
buh-bye.

16:14.140 --> 16:15.340
look, no offence,

16:15.407 --> 16:17.706
but we're going
to have to wrap this up,

16:17.773 --> 16:19.506
i don't have
flood insurance.

16:20.584 --> 16:24.414
i know that you
died in a ferry accident
in england.

16:24.515 --> 16:26.715
do you remember
anything about it?

16:27.886 --> 16:31.387
the water
took my breath away.

16:33.053 --> 16:35.120
i was so scared.

16:35.186 --> 16:36.717
i'm alone now.

16:36.718 --> 16:37.818
is there
something you need?

16:37.885 --> 16:39.119
someone i can contact?

16:39.185 --> 16:40.219
you can't help me.

16:40.285 --> 16:41.551
why not?

16:41.618 --> 16:43.052
i have to help you.

16:43.796 --> 16:45.562
how can you help me?

16:45.629 --> 16:47.328
is this a warning?

16:47.395 --> 16:49.899
are you trying to tell me
something about my friend?

16:49.900 --> 16:51.733
all eyes will be on you.

16:52.278 --> 16:54.045
what do you mean?

16:54.112 --> 16:56.878
i have to go
to the other place.

16:59.490 --> 17:00.790
ok...

17:04.255 --> 17:08.021
next time, bring a mop.

17:13.992 --> 17:16.626
you say she's been
doing this for how long?

17:16.693 --> 17:18.160
since the accident.

17:18.227 --> 17:21.726
every day,
every single day.

17:43.561 --> 17:45.793
can you ask her
why she keeps making these?

18:01.516 --> 18:03.412
she says she has to.

18:03.413 --> 18:07.480
it is in her head,
and she has to get it out.

18:30.123 --> 18:31.257
it's too girly.

18:31.323 --> 18:31.913
shush.

18:31.914 --> 18:34.151
what do you want,
football helmets
on the curtains?

18:34.152 --> 18:35.654
i don't want
curtains at all.

18:35.655 --> 18:36.655
why do you want
to cover the windows?

18:36.971 --> 18:37.976
i don't want to cover them,

18:37.977 --> 18:39.089
 i want to enhance them.

18:39.090 --> 18:40.690
this house has had
enough enhancement.

18:40.757 --> 18:42.720
when do we say,
"finished"?

18:42.721 --> 18:44.622
ah, never.

18:44.689 --> 18:45.955
why do i have the feeling

18:46.021 --> 18:47.622
that the words "never"
and "home improvement"

18:47.689 --> 18:48.888
go hand-in-hand
together, forever?

18:48.955 --> 18:49.589
you know what?

18:49.590 --> 18:50.857
you are very impatient.

18:50.924 --> 18:53.124
ok, it takes a while
to make a house a home.

18:53.551 --> 18:55.142
it took a while to make
this house a house.

18:55.201 --> 18:56.133
aren't you late for work?

18:56.700 --> 18:57.933
fine.

18:58.760 --> 18:59.786
you know
what my theory is?

18:59.787 --> 19:01.821
that window treatments
destroy marriages?

19:02.242 --> 19:03.775
well, yeah, that's
one of my theories.

19:03.842 --> 19:05.708
but...

19:05.775 --> 19:07.142
you're nervous,

19:07.209 --> 19:08.775
and you're
distracted by something,

19:08.842 --> 19:12.076
and that's why
the house is getting
another makeover.

19:12.142 --> 19:15.409
hmm, i was hoping
to appear industrious.

19:15.476 --> 19:17.276
well, you hoped wrong.

19:18.006 --> 19:21.359
i just keep getting
these weird visions,

19:21.360 --> 19:22.793
and there's
this strange ghost.

19:22.859 --> 19:24.193
strange ghost, huh?

19:25.011 --> 19:27.894
she keeps
showing me things,
and i don't know why.

19:27.895 --> 19:29.528
it's like she's sad
and in mourning.

19:29.595 --> 19:32.387
well, you think she's
trying to warn you
about something?

19:32.387 --> 19:34.162
i don't usually get
stuff about the future.

19:35.655 --> 19:36.897
you did last year.

19:36.898 --> 19:38.564
that turned out
to be right.

19:39.130 --> 19:40.361
i just know that i'm
not going to rest easy

19:40.362 --> 19:41.496
until
i can figure this out.

19:41.562 --> 19:42.763
and i will.

19:42.829 --> 19:44.196
and until then,
we get curtains?

19:44.262 --> 19:45.262
exactly!

21:31.731 --> 21:33.364
what is this place?

21:33.430 --> 21:34.996
part of it.

21:35.063 --> 21:36.163
of what?

21:36.664 --> 21:38.158
of what you have to know.

21:38.159 --> 21:39.992
what i have to show you.

21:41.416 --> 21:42.583
who sent you to me?

21:42.649 --> 21:44.999
they won't let me
see my husband.

21:45.523 --> 21:47.957
not until
i show you everything.

22:01.820 --> 22:03.309
so what do you think?

22:03.310 --> 22:04.390
how many times
do i have to explain

22:04.391 --> 22:06.024
the meaning of the word
"sabbatical" to you?

22:06.091 --> 22:07.457
definition--
leave with pay

22:07.524 --> 22:08.657
for teacher or professor

22:08.724 --> 22:10.958
for extended period
of study or rest.

22:11.024 --> 22:12.291
alternate definition--

22:12.358 --> 22:15.124
 an excuse for a confused
 and troubled man

22:15.191 --> 22:16.824
who wants to forget
about his real life

22:16.891 --> 22:19.691
and go and study
cicadas instead.

22:19.757 --> 22:21.791
don't forget
the "with pay" part.

22:21.857 --> 22:22.791
you know,
have you ever thought about

22:22.857 --> 22:24.557
new curtains
for this room?

22:24.624 --> 22:26.824
i don't think i've thought
about curtains, period.

22:27.768 --> 22:28.907
there might be more
to these visions

22:28.908 --> 22:30.074
than just
a ferry accident.

22:30.141 --> 22:31.507
well, you know what?

22:31.574 --> 22:33.607
these visions might not
be about just some ghost.

22:33.674 --> 22:35.607
you might have
a prophet ghost.

22:35.674 --> 22:36.607
ooh, that's a new one.

22:36.674 --> 22:38.074
prophet ghosts
are very common

22:38.141 --> 22:39.275
in all mythologies.

22:39.341 --> 22:41.574
i mean, ulysses
consulted a prophet ghost

22:41.641 --> 22:42.741
for homer's <i>odyssey.</i>

22:42.807 --> 22:43.774
native american traditions

22:43.841 --> 22:45.074
are rich
with prophet ghosts.

22:45.141 --> 22:46.774
let's not forget about
that rockin' trio--

22:46.841 --> 22:49.644
the ghosts of christmas
past, present, and future.

22:49.645 --> 22:50.845
so dickens knew about
the prophet ghosts

22:50.912 --> 22:51.797
and i don't?

22:51.798 --> 22:53.620
well, he didn't know
much about curtains,

22:53.621 --> 22:54.721
so i guess
it all evens out.

22:54.788 --> 22:55.954
can i just say
that this sabbatical

22:56.021 --> 22:57.287
has not improved
your mood?

22:57.719 --> 22:59.520
here's another theory.
how about this?

22:59.586 --> 23:01.752
how about your dreams aren't
really about the accidents.

23:01.819 --> 23:03.919
they're about the symbolism
behind the accidents.

23:03.986 --> 23:04.472
